<?php 
switch($verse){
case 1:{?>Alif. Lam. Mim.<?php break;}
case 2:{?>Do men imagine that they will be left ( at ease ) because they say, We believe, and will not be tested with affliction?<?php break;}
case 3:{?>Lo! We tested those who were before you. Thus Allah knoweth those who are sincere, and knoweth those who feign.<?php break;}
case 4:{?>Or do those who do ill deeds imagine that they can outstrip Us : Evil ( for them ) is that which they decide.<?php break;}
case 5:{?>Whoso looketh forward to the meeting with Allah ( let him know that ) Allah ' s reckoning is surely nigh, and He is the Hearer, the Knower.<?php break;}
case 6:{?>And whosoever striveth, striveth only for himself, for lo! Allah is altogether Independent of ( His ) creatures.<?php break;}
case 7:{?>And as for those who believe and do good works, We shall remit from them their evil deeds and shall repay them the best that they did.<?php break;}
case 8:{?>We have enjoined on man kindness to parents; but if they strive to make thee join with Me that of which thou past no knowledge, then obey them not. Unto Me is your return and I shall tell you what ye used to do.<?php break;}
case 9:{?>And as for those who believe and do good works, We verify shall make them enter in among the righteous.<?php break;}
case 10:{?>Of mankind is he who saith : We believe in Allah, but, if he be made to suffer for the sake of Allah, he mistaketh the persecution of mankind for Allah ' s punishment; and then, if victory cometh from thy Lord, will say : Lo! we were with you ( all the while ). Is not Allah best aware of what is in the bosoms of ( His ) creatures?<?php break;}
case 11:{?>Verily Allah knoweth those who believe, and verily He knoweth the hypocrites.<?php break;}
case 12:{?>Those who disbelieve say unto those who believe : Follow our way ( of religion ) and we verily will bear your sins ( for you ). They cannot bear aught of their sins. Lo! they verily are liars.<?php break;}
case 13:{?>But they verily will hear their own loads and other loads beside their own, and they verify will be questioned on the nay of Resurrection concerning that which they invented.<?php break;}
case 14:{?>And verify We sent Noah ( as Our messenger ) unto his folk, and he continued with them for a thousand years save fifty years; and the flood engulfed them, for they were wrongdoers.<?php break;}
case 15:{?>And We rescued him and those with him in the ship, and made of it a portent for the peoples.<?php break;}
case 16:{?>And Abraham! ( Remember ) when he said unto his folk : serve Allah, and keep your duty unto Him; that is better for you if ye did but know.<?php break;}
case 17:{?>Ye serve instead of Allah only idols, and ye only invent a lie. Lo! those whom ye serve instead of Allah own no provision for you. So seek your provision from Allah, and serve Him, and give thanks unto Him, ( for ) unto Him ye will be brought back.<?php break;}
case 18:{?>But if ye deny, then nations have denied before you. The messenger is only to convey ( the Message ) plainly.<?php break;}
case 19:{?>See they not how Allah produceth creation, then reproduceth it? Lo! for Allah that is easy.<?php break;}
case 20:{?>Say ( O Muhammad ) : Travel in the land and see how He originated creation, then Allah bringeth forth the later growth. Lo! Allah is Able to do all things.<?php break;}
case 21:{?>He punisheth whom He will and showeth mercy unto whom He will, and unto Him ye will be turned.<?php break;}
case 22:{?>Ye cannot escape ( from Him ) in the earth or in the sky, and beside Allah there is for you no friend nor helper.<?php break;}
case 23:{?>Those who disbelieve in the revelations of Allah and in ( their ) Meeting with Him, such have no hope of My mercy. For such there is a painful doom.<?php break;}
case 24:{?>But the answer of his folk was only that they said : "Kill him" or "Burn him. " Then Allah saved him from the fire. Lo! herein verily are portents for folk who believe.<?php break;}
case 25:{?>He said : Ye have chosen idols instead of Allah. The love between you is only in the life of the world. Then on the Day of Resurrection ye will deny each other and curse each other, and your abode will be the Fire, and ye will have no helpers.<?php break;}
case 26:{?>And Lot believed him, and said : Lo! I am a fugitive unto my Lord. Lo! He, only He, is the Mighty, the Wise.<?php break;}
case 27:{?>And We bestowed on him Isaac and Jacob, and We established the Prophethood and the Scripture among his seed, and We gave him his reward in the world, and lo! in the Hereafter he verily is among the righteous.<?php break;}
case 28:{?>And Lot! ( Remember ) when he said unto his folk : Lo! ye commit lewdness such as no creature did before you.<?php break;}
case 29:{?>For come ye not in unto males, and cut ye not the road ( for travellers ), and commit ye not abomination in your meetings? But the answer of his folk was only that they said : Bring Allah ' s doom upon us if thou art a truth teller!<?php break;}
case 30:{?>He said : My Lord! Give me victory over folk who work corruption.<?php break;}
case 31:{?>And when Our messengers brought Abraham the good news, they said : Lo! we are about to destroy the people of that township, for its people are wrong doers.<?php break;}
case 32:{?>He said : Lo! Lot is there. They said : We are best aware of who is there. We are to deliver him and his household, all save his wife, who is of those who stay behind.<?php break;}
case 33:{?>And when Our messengers came unto Lot, he was troubled upon their account, for he could not protect them; but they said : Fear not, nor grieve! Lo! we are to deliver thee and thy household, ( all ) save thy wife, who is of those who stay behind.<?php break;}
case 34:{?>Lo! we are about to bring down upon folk of this township a fury from the sky because they are evil livers.<?php break;}
case 35:{?>And verily of that We have left a clear sign for people who have sense.<?php break;}
case 36:{?>And unto Midian We sent Shueyb, their brother. He said O my people! Serve Allah, and look forward to the Last Day, and do not evil, making mischief, in the earth.<?php break;}
case 37:{?>But they denied him, and the dreadful earthquake took them, and morning found them prostrate in their dwelling place.<?php break;}
case 38:{?>And ( the tribes of ) Aad and Thamud! ( Their fate ) is manifest unto you from their ( ruined and deserted ) dwellings. Satan made their deeds seem fair unto them and so debarred them from the Way, though they were keen observers.<?php break;}
case 39:{?>And Korah, Pharaoh and Haman! Moses came unto them with clear proofs ( of Allah ' s sovereignty ), but they were boastful in the land. And they were not winners ( in the race ).<?php break;}
case 40:{?>So We took each one in his sin; of them was he on whom We sent a hurricane, and of them was he who was overtaken by the ( Awful ) Cry, and of them was he whom We caused the earth to swallow, and of them was he whom We drowned. It was not for Allah to wrong them, but they wronged themselves.<?php break;}
case 41:{?>The likeness of those who choose other patrons than Allah is as the likeness of the spider when she taketh unto herself a house, and lo! the frailest of all houses is the spider ' s house, if they but knew.<?php break;}
case 42:{?>Lo! Allah knoweth what thing they invoke instead of Him. He is the Mighty, the Wise.<?php break;}
case 43:{?>As for these similitudes, We coin them for mankind, but none will grasp their meaning save the wise.<?php break;}
case 44:{?>Allah created the heavens and the earth with truth. Lo! therein is indeed a portent for believers.<?php break;}
case 45:{?>Recite that which hath been inspired in thee of the Scripture, and establish worship. Lo! worship preserveth from lewdness and iniquity, but verily remembrance of Allah is more important. And Allah knoweth what ye do.<?php break;}
case 46:{?>And argue not with the People of the Scripture unless it be in ( a way ) that is better, save with such of them as do wrong; and say : We believe in that which hath been revealed unto us and revealed unto you; our God and your God is One, and unto Him we surrender.<?php break;}
case 47:{?>In like manner We have revealed unto thee the Scripture, and those unto whom We gave the Scripture aforetime will believe therein; and of these ( also ) there are some who believe therein. And none deny our revelations save the disbelievers<?php break;}
case 48:{?>And thou ( O Muhammad ) wast not a reader of any scripture before it, nor didst thou write it with thy right hand, for then might those have doubted, who follow falsehood.<?php break;}
case 49:{?>But it is clear revelations in the hearts of those who have been given knowledge, and none deny our revelations save wrong doers.<?php break;}
case 50:{?>And they say : Why are not portents sent down upon him from his Lord? Say : Portents are with Allah only, and I am but a plain warner.<?php break;}
case 51:{?>Is it not enough for them that We have sent down unto thee the Scripture which is read unto them? Lo! herein verily is mercy, and a reminder for folk who believe.<?php break;}
case 52:{?>Say ( unto them, O Muhammad ) : Allah sufficeth for witness between me and you. He knoweth whatsoever is in the heavens and the earth. And those who believe in vanity and disbelieve in Allah, they it is who are the losers.<?php break;}
case 53:{?>They bid thee hasten on the doom ( of Allah ). And if a term had not been appointed, the doom would assuredly have come unto them ( ere now ). And verily it will come upon them suddenly when they perceive not.<?php break;}
case 54:{?>They bid thee hasten on the doom, when lo! hell verily will encompass the disbelievers.<?php break;}
case 55:{?>On the day when the doom will overwhelm them from above them and from underneath their feet, and He will say : Taste what ye used to do!<?php break;}
case 56:{?>O my bondmen who believe! Lo! My earth is spacious. Therefor serve Me only.<?php break;}
case 57:{?>Every soul will taste of death. Then unto Us ye will be returned.<?php break;}
case 58:{?>Those who believe and do good works, them verily We shall house in lofty dwellings of the Garden underneath which rivers flow. There they will dwell secure. How sweet the guerdon of the toilers,<?php break;}
case 59:{?>Who persevere, and put their trust in their Lord!<?php break;}
case 60:{?>And how many an animal there is that beareth not its own provision! Allah provideth for it and for you. He is the Hearer, the Knower.<?php break;}
case 61:{?>And if thou wert to ask them : Who created the heavens and the earth, and constrained the sun and the moon ( to their appointed work )? they would say : Allah. How then are they turned away?<?php break;}
case 62:{?>Allah maketh the provision wide for whom He will of His bondmen, and straiteneth it for whom ( He will ). Lo! Allah is Aware of all things.<?php break;}
case 63:{?>And if thou wert to ask them : Who causeth water to come down from the sky, and therewith reviveth the earth after its death? they verily would say : Allah. Say : Praise be to Allah! But most of them have no sense.<?php break;}
case 64:{?>This life of the world is but a pastime and a game. Lo! the home of the Hereafter that is Life, if they but knew.<?php break;}
case 65:{?>And when they mount upon the ships they pray to Allah, making their faith pure for Him only, but when He bringeth them safe to land, behold! they ascribe partners ( unto Him ),<?php break;}
case 66:{?>That they may disbelieve in that which We have given them, and that they may take their ease. But they will come to know.<?php break;}
case 67:{?>Have they not seen that We have appointed a sanctuary immune ( from violence ), while mankind are ravaged all around them? Do they then believe in falsehood and disbelieve in the bounty of Allah?<?php break;}
case 68:{?>Who doeth greater wrong than he who inventeth a lie concerning Allah, or denieth the truth when it cometh unto him? Is not there a home in hell for disbelievers?<?php break;}
case 69:{?>As for those who strive in Us, We surely guide them to Our paths, and lo! Allah is with the good.<?php break;}
}?>